<documentation title="Warn about PHP close tag at end of file">
  <standard>
    <![CDATA[
If the PHP close tag '?>' is detected at the end of a file, a warning is raised.
If the PHP close tag is detected at the end of a file, and there is whitespace after it, an error is raised.

This is because the PHP close tag at the end of the file can produce undesirable output.
    ]]>
  </standard>
</documentation>
